-- Ecuador Says Spain Will Provide $260 Million of Aid Over Four-Year Period
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2010-10-14T18:23:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/ecuador-says-spain-will-provide-260-million-of-aid-over-four-year-period.html
Ecuador said Spain will give it $260
million in aid over four years for development measures focused
on the South American country’s poor.  Spain will donate $65 million per year for projects
including improved access to potable water, according to a
statement published today on the Ecuadorean president’s website.
The agreement will be signed in the “coming days,” the
statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
